comment.shortText:
This class is used to keep the bots various properties separate from
the discord.js Client class.
```js
const bot = new BotClient(options)
```
Creates an instance of BotClient.

Used to run some basic dev related logging, such as discord debugging
```js
if (process.env.NODE_ENV !== 'production') bot.dev();
```

This method is used to start the bots initialization process
```js
without sentry support.
bot.init(String(process.env.TOKEN));
with sentry support.
bot.init(String(process.env.TOKEN), Sentry);
```

comment.text: Send sentry through so it can be used by the bot

comment.shortText:
The DiscordClient class is a special class it's effectively the discord.js
Client class but with a magic circular reference to the BotClient class (bot).
```javascript
new DiscordClient(options, bot)
```

tags.text: The only time this class should be called is in the BotClient class.

comment.shortText: Creates an instance of DiscordClient.
Sets or gets the default captureRejection value for all emitters.

This symbol shall be used to install a listener for only monitoring `'error'`
events. Listeners installed using this symbol are called before the regular
`'error'` listeners are called.
comment.text:
Installing a listener using this symbol does not change the behavior once an
`'error'` event is emitted, therefore the process will still crash if no
regular `'error'` listener is installed.
